value.title: Glenn Greenwald leaves The Intercept, claiming he was ‘censored’ over an article he wrote on Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Journalist Glenn Greenwald said Thursday that he was leaving The Intercept, the news website he helped found, claiming that it had refused to publish an article he wrote on Joe Biden unless he removed sections that were critical of the Democratic presidential nominee.

value.title: Retired Minnesota police officers asked to be Trump poll watchers in 'rough neighborhoods'
value.excerpt: A volunteer attorney for the Trump 2020 campaign is seeking retired officers to work as poll challengers in Minnesota.

value.title: Former Michigan Gov. Rick Snyder on being a 'proud Republican' who voted for Biden
value.excerpt: Snyder served eight years as governor and was replaced by Democrat Gretchen Whitmer in 2019.

value.title: Chuck Todd Slammed For Saying Joe Biden Takes COVID-19 'Too Seriously'
value.excerpt: The MSNBC host said that Biden was accepting a smaller footprint by not engaging in high-risk campaign acitivities

value.title: Trump administration removes gray wolf from endangered species list
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is dropping the gray wolf from the endangered species list under the assertion that the animal's population has sufficiently recovered, a move conservation groups decry as shortsighted and promise to challenge in court.

value.title: Biden, Cunningham hold narrow leads in North Carolina: poll
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden has a narrow lead over President Trump in North Carolina, while Democrat Cal Cunningham holds a similarly slim lead in the Tarheel State’s marquee Senate race in a new survey released Thursday.

value.title: Trump Warns ‘Bad Things’ Will Happen To ‘Treasonous’ Ex-Official Miles Taylor
value.excerpt: After calling for Taylor to be prosecuted for an anonymous 2018 op-ed, Trump extended his call to the New York Times for publishing it.

value.title: Pence stumps for vulnerable GOP senators resisting Democrat takeover
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is campaigning with four GOP senators this week in an effort to boost their precarious standing in races that will help determine which party controls the upper chamber of Congress.

value.title: Biden and Cunningham Hold Slim Leads in North Carolina, Poll Finds
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Cal Cunningham both led their Republican rivals by three points, a Times/Siena College survey found. Perhaps most notably, 64 percent of respondents said they had already voted.

value.title: WATCH: Joe Biden holds drive-in rally in Tampa, Florida
value.excerpt: Both nominees are now focusing on encouraging voters to turn out in person on Election Day, next Tuesday. More than 73 million Americans have already voted, either by absentee or by mail.

value.title: Biden dismisses record economic growth as not 'nearly enough' to dig out of 'deep' recession
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden dismissed the U.S. economy's record-shattering growth as not "nearly enough" to get the country out of a "deep hole" on Thursday.

value.title: Former Democrat Rubin on why he is voting for Trump: 'No feeling of patriotism' on the left anymore
value.excerpt: President Trump is the last bastion to stopping the radical left, talk show host Dave Rubin said Thursday.

value.title: Hackers Stole $2.3 Million From Trump Reelection Account In Wisconsin
value.excerpt: Hackers have taken $2.3 million from the Wisconsin Republican Party’s account supporting Trump’s reelection, the party’s chairman told The Associated Press on Thursday, a campaign disruption in the critical swing state less than a week from Election Day.

value.title: Joe Biden is a 'Trojan Horse' for socialism, says Tammy Bruce
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden is being used as a "trojan horse," Fox News contributor Tammy Bruce said on Thursday.

value.title: Wisconsin GOP says hackers stole $2.3M from Trump reelection fund
value.excerpt: Hackers stole $2.3 million from the Wisconsin Republican Party's account that was being used to help reelect President Donald Trump in the key battleground state, the party's chairman told The Associated Press on Thursday.

value.title: Mike Pence holds rally at Des Moines airport, as Election Day approaches
value.excerpt: Five days before Election Day and with early voting in Iowa well underway, Vice President Mike Pence will hold a rally Thursday at the Des Moines International Airport. Doors open for the "Make America Great Again" rally at 11:30 a.m. The event is ...

value.title: Ari Fleischer: Why my 2020 choice for president will be Donald Trump
value.excerpt: In many ways, I find President Trump over-the-top and offensive, and have said so on-the-air and on Twitter. He can be too hot to handle, insulting people and too often making himself the issue, diverting attention from more important policy matters.

value.title: Biden vows to pass LGBTQ rights legislation in first 100 days
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden has promised to make the Equality Act a "top legislative priority" should he win Tuesday’s election.

value.title: Mike Pence in Wilmington: Choice is 'Whether America remains America'
value.excerpt: The vice president spoke during a campaign visit to Wilmington where he addressed the current administration's record and urged attendants to vote.

value.title: Watch: Trump rushes Sen. Martha McSally on stage during Arizona rally
value.excerpt: During a campaign rally in Goodyear, Ariz., President Donald Trump rushed Republican Senator Martha McSally on stage to speak. McSally is in a close Senate race with her Democratic challenger astronaut Mark Kelly.

value.title: They call themselves 'Wives of the Deplorables' because their husbands support Trump
value.excerpt: Carole Catherine did not know her husband, Tim, supported Donald Trump until the day after Hillary Clinton lost the 2016 election. She called him the next morning crying.

value.title: Joe Biden: We can restore the soul of our nation | Raleigh News & Observer
value.excerpt: The Editorial Board invited both presidential candidates to make their case to voters.

value.title: US Air Force F-16s intercepted an unauthorized aircraft flying in a restricted area over a Trump rally
value.excerpt: When President Donald Trump saw the F-16 deploy signal flares, he told a crowd that they were putting on a display for him.

value.title: Watch: Barack Obama Campaigns For Joe Biden At Orlando, Florida Event
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama will campaign for Joe Biden at an Orlando, Florida event on Tuesday afternoon, one week ahead of the 2020 election.

value.title: Trump Jr. warns election is 'about freedom versus tyranny, capitalism versus socialism and Communism'
value.excerpt: The Democrats' "endgame" is to transform America into a far-left, Marxist state where dissent is not permitted, Donald Trump Jr. told "Hannity" Wednesday night.
